OL,3,CTop Labour councillor quits party over
OL,4,Cwelfare cuts
OL,6,F"I cannot attack the Tories in Dudley
OL,7,Ffor cutting support for the most
OL,8,Fvulnerable, whilst staying silent when
OL,9,Fthe Government does the same. The
OL,10,FLabour Party has lost its soul."
OL,12,FHis decision follows radical welfare
OL,13,Freform proposals from Work and
OL,14,FPensions Secretary Liz Kendall, which
OL,15,Fseek to tighten eligibility for
OL,16,Fdisability benefits and overhaul the
OL,17,FUniversal Credit system.
