OL,3,CTop Labour councillor quits party over
OL,4,Cwelfare cuts
OL,6,FThe government claims the reforms will
OL,7,Fhelp more people into work and save #5
OL,8,Fbillion by 2030, but critics argue
OL,9,Fthey disproportionately affect those
OL,10,Fwho are unable to work due to illness
OL,11,For disability.
OL,13,FLowe's resignation is the latest blow
OL,14,Fto Labour in Dudley, where the party
OL,15,Fremains in a fragile position
OL,16,Ffollowing last year's local elections.
OL,18,FIn 2024 the Conservatives and Labour
OL,19,Fboth won 34 seats each, with the
OL,20,FTories continuing to run the council
OL,21,Fdespite it being in no overall control.
